President Biden is set to welcome Prime Minister Kyriakos Mitsotakis of Greece to the White House on May 16, 2022. The visit will serve as an opportunity to strengthen the bilateral partnership between the two countries and commemorate 201 years of Greek independence. The leaders will discuss ongoing efforts with Allies and partners to support Ukraine and impose economic costs on Russia for its aggression. They will also address global challenges such as climate change and energy security. Additionally, they will review joint endeavors to promote global security through NATO and work towards peace and prosperity in the region. The visit will also celebrate the historical, democratic, and trade relations that have connected Greece and the United States for generations.